    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-02T13:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-02T13:45:00-05:00" n="907"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/7679: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-02T13:00:00-05:45"
                            >January 2, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Dr. <persName corresp="#p_SJB2">Sacasa</persName> was inaugurated President
                    the morning of January 1st and <persName corresp="#p_MMGCB1">General
                        Matthews</persName> turned over command of the Guardia Nacional to
                    Nicaraguan officers immediately thereafter. Evacuation of United States forces
                    from Eastern Nicaragua completed by United <pb facs="1029" n="925"
                        xml:id="pg_925"/> States Ship <hi rend="italic">Overton</hi> January 1st.
                    First contingent of aeroplanes left Managua January 1st; final contingent left
                    this morning. All remaining United States forces are now en route by rail to
                    Corinto where they will be evacuated today by the United States Ship <hi
                        rend="italic">Henderson</hi> and the United States Ship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Antares</hi>. The United States Ship <hi rend="italic">Memphis</hi> will
                    also depart from Corinto today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HME1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
